%C A127929 Aside from "3", all terms of A127928 must be 1 or 7 mod 18 (see A127928 for mod rules); but not all primes mod 1 or 7 are pure hailstone numbers. For example, the prime 61 == 7 mod 18 but 61 is impure. Conjecture: for large n, the numbers of 1 and 7 mod 18 terms are approximately equal.
